subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-09-28T08:30:13Z","updated_at":"2022-09-28T08:33:32Z","body":"> @mperham Hi, is there a way to customize DJQ size?\r\n\r\n```\r\nSidekiq.configure_server do |config|\r\n  config.options[:dead_max_jobs] = 100_000\r\n  config.options[:dead_timeout_in_seconds] = 15_552_000\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n_Sidekiq does not store unlimited number of jobs in Dead queue forever. By default, right after adding a new job to the Dead queue, it removes all but last 10_000 dead jobs (`Sidekiq.options[:dead_max_jobs]`), it also removes all dead jobs older than 6 months (`Sidekiq.options[:dead_timeout_in_seconds]`)._","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sidekiq/sidekiq/issues/comments/1260566565/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"artamonovdev","id":16417925,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2NDE3OTI1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16417925?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev","html_url":"https://github.com/artamonovdev","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/artamonovdev/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.gith